 - in such circumstances, it would appear unproductive for the Trump administration to provide notice of intent to withdraw before the Mexican elections;
 - could they conclude the last round before Oct 1 (yes), and is it likely to be successful? (probably no, if the US does not moderate its demands). But this is a narrow window. 
 - if the negotiations fail, is it likely that the Trump administration will provide the notice? I think "yes", otherwise they would lose both face and credibility domestically.  So this question will resolve as "yes" if (i) the negotiations are concluded well before Oct 1 (I assign 20% here); (ii) they fail (75%). This brings me to 15% in total.
